          <h2 class="item-title">
           Guitar Player Repair Guide
          </h2>
          <div class="left-column">
           <article class="article">
            <p>
             <b>
              By Dan Erlewine
             </b>
             <br/>
             The leading step-by-step manual for every guitar owner.
             <br/>
             <b class="cff0000">
              Only at StewMac: Dan Erlewine will autograph your copy!
             </b>
            </p>
            <p>
             <b class="cff0000">
              Updated 3rd edition:
             </b>
             <br/>
             <b>
              FREE! Guitar Tips DVD
             </b>
             shows you how to evaluate, intonate and string a guitar.
             <br/>
             <b>
              NEW: content sorting
             </b>
             tailors the information to all skill levels.
             <br/>
             <br/>
            </p>
            <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
             <tr>
              <td style="width:87">
               <img alt="Content based on your skill level" border="0" height="130" src="/catalog/product_detail/0570_detail01.gif" width="87"/>
              </td>
              <td>
               The basic sections keep your guitar out of the repair shop and playing its best.
               <br/>
               <br/>
               For the do-it-yourselfer: how to do both simple and advanced repairs.
               <br/>
               <br/>
               Want to go even further into guitar repair? The deep sections are for you.
              </td>
             </tr>
            </table>
            <br/>
            <br/>
            322 pages, softcover.
            <br/>
            <br/>
            <b>
             "A common-sense guide in layman's terms."
             <br/>
            </b>
            Chris Martin, CEO, Martin Guitars
            <br/>
            <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
             <tr>
              <td>
               <b>
                "This book is a must-have."
               </b>
               <br/>
               Henry Juszkiewicz
               <br/>
               Chairman, Gibson Guitars
               <br/>
               <br/>
               <b>
                "It's been 14 years since the previous edition, and my old copy's
                <span class="red">
                 overflowing
                </span>
                with notes and new techniques! I've included all of that in this update!"
               </b>
               <img align="right" alt="Dan" border="0" src="/catalog/product_detail/0570_detail03.gif"/>
              </td>
              <td width="10">
              </td>
              <td>
               <img alt="Guitar Player Repair Guide" border="0" src="/catalog/product_detail/0570_detail02.jpg"/>
              </td>
             </tr>
            </table>
            <br/>
            <b>
             <span class="red">
              Free DVD included.
             </span>
            </b>
            Dan shows you how to evaluate any guitar before buying, how to set your own intonation (it's simple!) and how to install strings without damaging your guitar.
            <br/>
            <br/>
            <img alt="Free guitar assessment forms" src="/catalog/product_detail/0570_detail04.gif"/>
            <br/>
            <br/>
            <b>
             <span class="red">
              Free printable forms for repair shops.
             </span>
            </b>
            Computer files are included on the DVD: guitar assessment forms for repair work in printable PDF format.
            <br/>
            <br/>
            <b>
             <span class="red">
              These are just SOME of the topics covered:
             </span>
            </b>
            <br/>
            Action and setups
            <br/>
            Nuts, saddles
            <br/>
            Fret work
            <br/>
            Tuners, tremolos
            <br/>
            Bridges, braces
            <br/>
            Bodies, necks
            <br/>
            Finishing repairs
            <br/>
            Structural repairs
            <br/>
            Electronics
            <br/>
            <b>
             Lots more!
            </b>
            <br/>
            <br/>
            The
            <b>
             Guitar Player Repair Guide
            </b>
            is the most widely used basic reference in repair shops, featuring factory setup specifications for Martin, Gibson and Fender guitars, in-depth fretting instruction, advice from top repairmen, and much more! The book grew out of Dan's popular Guitar Player magazine columns. Now in its 3rd edition, it includes lots of recent techniques Dan discovered while repairing every kind of guitar, from the new and inexpensive to the vintage and priceless. 322 pages, softcover.
            <br/>
           </article>

    function RR_openImage(url) {
        var reviewImageHolder = document.getElementById("RR_reviewImageHolder");
        reviewImageHolder.innerHTML = '&lt;img src="' + url + '" style="max-height: 800px;" /&gt;';

        var backgroundDiv = document.getElementById("RR_shadeBackgroundForImage");
        var displayDiv = document.getElementById("RR_reviewImageMiddle");
        var outerDiv = document.getElementById("RR_reviewImageOuter");

        backgroundDiv.style.visibility = "visible";

        var windowHeight = (window.innerHeight != null ? window.innerHeight : document.documentElement &amp;&amp; document.documentElement.clientHeight ? document.documentElement.clientHeight : document.body != null ? document.body.clientHeight : null);

        if (windowHeight &gt; outerDiv.clientHeight) {
            //outerDiv.style.top = ((windowHeight - outerDiv.clientHeight) / 2) + 'px';
            outerDiv.style.top = '20%';
        }
        else {
            outerDiv.style.top = '0px';
        }

        displayDiv.style.visibility = "visible";
    }

    function RR_closeImage() {
        var displayDiv = document.getElementById("RR_reviewImageMiddle");
        displayDiv.style.visibility = "hidden";

        var shadeDiv = document.getElementById("RR_shadeBackgroundForImage");
        shadeDiv.style.visibility = "hidden";

        var reviewImageHolder = document.getElementById("RR_reviewImageHolder");
        reviewImageHolder.innerHTML = "&nbsp;";
    }

    function RR_SendFeedbackCommentFeedbackResponse(fbc_key,fcr_code, promptandbuttonsid, loadingid, responseid) {
        var returnValue = -55;
        this.feedbackcommentkey= fbc_key;
        this.feedbackcommentresponse = fcr_code;

        var returnValue = -55;
        if (typeof(wsHelper) != "undefined") {
            $('#' + promptandbuttonsid).css('display', 'none');
            $('#' + loadingid).css('display', 'block');
            
            wsHelper.SendFeedbackCommentFeedbackResponse(this.feedbackcommentkey, this.feedbackcommentresponse, function(returnValue) {
            
                $('#' + loadingid).css('display', 'none');

                if (returnValue == -200)
                {
                    $('#' + responseid).css('display', 'block');

                    
                    $('#' + responseid).html('You already left feedback on this comment!');
                    
                }
                else if (returnValue == 0) {
                    $('#' + responseid).css('display', 'block');
                }
                else {
                    $('#' + responseid).css('display', 'block');

                    
                    $('#' + responseid).html('There was a problem with your feedback about this comment');
                    
                }
            }, function(error) {
            
                $('#' + loadingid).css('display', 'none');
                $('#' + responseid).css('display', 'block');

                
                $('#' + responseid).html('There was a problem with your feedback about this comment');
                
            });
            
        }

        //alert('feedbackcommentkey is: ' + this.feedbackcommentkey + ', feedbackcommentresponse is: ' + this.feedbackcommentresponse + ', and return value is: ' + returnValue);
    }

                $('#imagePreviewData').attr('src', $('#ctl00_mPageContent_AddFeedbackComment_hFeedbackImage').attr('value'));
                $('#imagePreviewData').css('visibility', 'visible');

                $('#imagePreviewData').load(function() {
                    if ($('#ctl00_mPageContent_AddFeedbackComment_hFeedbackImageResize').val() &amp;&amp; $('#ctl00_mPageContent_AddFeedbackComment_hFeedbackImageResizeHeight').attr('value') != '' &amp;&amp; $('#ctl00_mPageContent_AddFeedbackComment_hFeedbackImageResizeWidth').attr('value') != '') {

                        var thumbwidth = $('#ctl00_mPageContent_AddFeedbackComment_hFeedbackImageResizeWidth').attr('value');

                        console.log("thumbheight:" + thumbheight);
                        console.log("thumbwidth:" + thumbwidth);

                        var height = $('#imagePreviewData').height();
                        var width = $('#imagePreviewData').width();

                        console.log("height:" + height);
                        console.log("width:" + width);

                        var ratio = thumbwidth / thumbheight;

                        if ((thumbheight * ratio) &gt; thumbwidth) {
                            thumbheight = (thumbwidth / ratio);
                        }
                        else if ((thumbheight * ratio) &lt; thumbwidth) {
                            thumbwidth = (thumbheight * ratio);
                        }

                        $('#imagePreviewData').css('height', thumbheight);
                        $('#imagePreviewData').css('width', thumbwidth);

                        console.log("thumbheight:" + thumbheight);
                        console.log("thumbwidth:" + thumbwidth);

                        console.log("hFeedbackImage's value: " + $('#ctl00_mPageContent_AddFeedbackComment_hFeedbackImage').attr('value'));

                    }
                });

                //readURL($("#feedbackFileUploaded"));

            else {
                $('#imagePreviewData').css('visibility', 'hidden');
            }
        }

    function readURL(input) {
        if (input &amp;&amp; input.files &amp;&amp; input.files[0]) {
            var reader = new FileReader();

            reader.onload = function (e) {
                $('#ctl00_mPageContent_AddFeedbackComment_hFeedbackImage').attr('value', e.target.result);
                console.log(e.target.result);
            }

            reader.readAsDataURL(input.files[0]);

            var file = input.files[0];
            var filename = file.name;
            var contenttype = file.type;
            
            $('#ctl00_mPageContent_AddFeedbackComment_hFeedbackImageFileName').attr('value', filename);
            $('#ctl00_mPageContent_AddFeedbackComment_hFeedbackImageContentType').attr('value', contenttype);
